== Connective tissue dysplasia syndrome ==

Marfan Syndrome - a genetic defect in 15 pairs of chromosomes, resulting in disturbed synthesis of fibrillin, which is one of the main components of fibro-elastic connective tissue
Ehlers-Danlos syndrome - a congenital defect of the connective tissue. One of its forms (type IV) is associated with severe pathology of the cardiovascular system



=== Leading cause of death in Marfan's syndrome - cardiovascular complications  ===

Dilatation of the aortic root - (cause of death in 75 - 85%) 
Occlusion of the mouths of the coronary arteries Exfoliating aortic 
Prolapse and mitral regurgitation 
Dilatation of the left ventricle and heart failure 
Aortic valve insufficiency as a result of aortic root dilatation 
The risk of aortic rupture increases significantly when the diameter of the aorta is greater than 5.5 cm 


==Pathophysiology==

*Initial lesion is a [[fatty streak]] in [[Tunica intima|intimal layer]].
*Intermediate phase of insufficiency formation is [[smooth muscle]] [[Cell growth|proliferation]].
*Final phase of formation is a [[Atherosclerotic_plaques|fibrous plaque]] overlying a soft tissue core of [[lipids]] and [[necrotic]] debris.

==Diagnosis==

*Inspection may reveal [[muscle atrophy]] from disuse, trophic skin changes ([[loss of hair]], [[dry skin]]), or thickened nails.
*[[Arterial_insufficiency_ulcer|Ulcers]] or [[gangrene]] is present in [[Acute_limb_ischemia|critical limb ischemia]].
*Pulses should be palpated in the [[femoral artery|femoral]], [[popliteal artery|popliteal]], [[dorsalis pedis]], and [[posterior tibial artery|posterior tibial]] positions.

===Lab tests===

*Routine [[Medical_laboratory|laboratory tests]] show no changes
*Serum chemistry (complete [[blood count]], including [[platelet count]]; [[lipid profile]]; fasting [[blood glucose]] and [[hemoglobin]] A1C; [[creatinine|BUN/creatinine]]; [[homocysteine]])
*Noninvasive vascular laboratory
**Segmental limb pressures, [[Doppler_ultrasound|Doppler]] waveform analysis
**[[Treadmill]] testing
**Toe [[plethysmography]] and pressures 
**[[Medical_ultrasonography|Duplex]]

===Imaging===

*[[Angiography|Contrast angiography]]
